quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  2,154,"Do not say: \"They are dead!\" about anyone who is killed for God´s sake. Rather they are living, even though you do not notice it"
  2,155,"We shall test you with a bit of fear and hunger, plus a shortage of wealth and souls and produce. Announce such to patient people"
  2,156,"who say, whenever some misfortune strikes them: \"We belong to God, and are returning to Him"
  2,157,"Such will have their prayers [accepted] by their Lord, and [granted] mercy. Those have consented to be guided"
  2,158,"Safa and Marwa are some of God´s waymarks. Anyone who goes on Pilgrimage to the House or visits [it] will not be blamed if he runs along between them. With anyone who volunteers some good, God is Appreciative, Aware"
  2,159,"God curses those who hide whatever We send down explanations and guidance, once We have explained it to mankind in the Book, and cursers will curse them"
  2,160,"except for those who repent, reform and explain; those I accept repentance from, for I am the Receiver Repentance, the Merciful"
  2,161,"Those who disbelieve and die while they are disbelievers will have God´s curse upon them, as well as the angels´ and all mankind´s"
  2,162,to live forever. Torment will not be lightened for them will they be allowed to wait
  2,163,"Your God is God Alone there is no deity except Him, the Mercy-giving, the Merciful"